aminations taken by Missouri high schools increased by 70 percent from 6913 to 11 757 between 1995 and 2001 Chart 2 In 2001 69 0 percent of the AP examinations written by Missouri students earned a score of three or above on a five point scale ranking Missouri 6th nationally in performance on the AP exams Chart 1 High Schools Offering Advanced Placement Chart 2 Missouri Students Participation in AP While the College Board recommends that students should receive college credit if they achieve scores of 3 or above Missouri institutions determine their own policies regarding credit and advanced placement for AP scores see a list of institutional policies at http www2 truman edu ap http www2 truman edu ap The CBHE recommends that students contact institutions directly about questions concerning AP acceptance policies Missouri s Support of AP The CBHE began supporting AP with budget recommendations in FY97 Since the fall 1996 Missouri has funded two AP Teacher Development APTD sites one at http www2 truman edu 7Ehartsock apnews htm Truman State University and one at http cstl semo edu aptd Southeast Missouri State University In recognition of the importance of AP in the state s education landscape the http www dese state mo us divimprove gifted index html Department of Elementary and Secondary Education DESE has also committed significant resources to enhancing students access to AP exams Using the DESE link above click on the Advanced Placement link in the first paragraph thin banner gif Missouri Department of Higher Education 3515 Amazonas Dr Jefferson City MO 65109 5717 Phone 573 751 2361 Fax 573 751 6635 MOSTARS Information Center 800 473 6757 Technical questions about the Web site mailto webmaster dhe mo gov please contact us This page was last updated Mon 03 Nov 2003 10 20 22
